        "summary": "Rescuers 'pulling people out with their bare hands' as earthquakes kill 920 - BBC News Summary This live coverage has ended - for the latest updates head to our new page The number of people killed in two Venezuelan earthquakes has risen to at least 920, with 3,360 injured, according to officials In Caracas, overwhelmed rescuers are \"pulling people out with their bare hands\" , a student tells the BBC Natacha Diaz, a mother of two missing women, says her daughters \"are all I have\" - watch what else she says Others are also trying to reach their relatives - Marianella tells BBC News Mundo \"my heart tells me my brother is alive\" International rescue teams, bringing along sniffer dogs , have joined the search for survivors The quakes, with magnitudes of 7.2 and 7.5, hit a minute apart on Wednesday night, and the second was the strongest to hit Venezuela since 1900 - here's what else we know You can also follow the latest updates on BBC News Mundo Previous Next 0:47 Relatives search through rubble in La Guaira. 00:00:47, play video Relatives search through rubble in La Guaira 0:38 '10,000 body bags' procured - UN coordinator. 00:00:38, play video '10,000 body bags' procured - UN coordinator 1:15 Earthquake survivors shelter in baseball stadium. 00:01:15, play video Earthquake survivors shelter in baseball stadium 1:32 Families search for loved ones outside Caracas hospital. 00:01:32, play video Families search for loved ones outside Caracas hospital 1:39 'The stench of death is overpowering at times' 00:01:39, play video 'The stench of death is overpowering at times' 1:19 Venezuelans angry at state-led rescue efforts. 00:01:19, play video Venezuelans angry at state-led rescue efforts 0:46 Baby and mother pulled alive from collapsed building. 00:00:46, play video Baby and mother pulled alive from collapsed building 1:13 Panic attacks and fractures at Caracas hospital. 00:01:13, play video Panic attacks and fractures at Caracas hospital 0:41 Man d